info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 19 at 10:11PM PST until January 20 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST FRIDAY... * WHAT...North winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph. * WHERE...Santa Barbara County Southwestern Coast, Santa Ynez Mountains Western Range and Santa Ynez Mountains Eastern Range. * WHEN...Until 4 AM PST Friday. * IMPACTS...Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. This includes Highway 33 in Ventura County as well as Interstate 5 and Highway 14 in Los Angeles County.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
